rComments: Very sweet prof and is very understanding. There are participation marks for the course, and she doesnt want people to feel nervous about speaking french aloud, so she doesnt pick on people. Very kind and helps us with specific difficult concepts in french and spends extra time if we need it even if we are falling behind.

Rosa is an amazing professor and her lectures are really profound. If you do all the readings and come to class prepared your mark will reflect it. I've taken two courses from her and they were both great!!
A very helpful, kind, and fair professor. Like others have remarked, she really wants to see her students succeed and CARES about our success.
Best French professor I've had at U of T. Actually WANTS all of her students to do well and succeed.

A very nice prof., if you feel nervous about your French, then take her course b/c she doesn't put you on the spot and she's very understanding. I respect that she tries to make her classes creative and fun. If you show that you're making an effort, then you're good in her books. Fair marker-not lenient.
